  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause defines the parties' roles and operating structure, but lacks detail on financial risk management mechanisms for the non-operator.",
  "operative_text": "This agreement details the relationship between BOSCH and CLIENT as two separate companies operating independently of each other. BOSCH reserves the right to keep product generation and delivery confidential, limiting audit access. BOSCH also retains the right to share rights unless it disrupts or interferes with CLIENT's business.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks detail on financial risk management mechanisms for the non-operator in case of unforeseen circumstances. This could lead to financial strain for the non-operator if a capital call (effec (effectiveness 20%, seen 1x) is not handled transparently.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["BOSCH", "CLIENT"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "non-operator"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause defines the 'Product' and its name, but lacks details on joint venture responsibilities, financial obligations, or risk allocation.",
  "operative_text": "This clause defines the 'Product' and its name, BOSCH has acquired, developed and continues to develop a business using proprietary \"Nano Printed Lights\", and associated other products (the \"Products\"). BOSCH calls this Nano Printed Lights product \"Printed LightSheets\" which is considered the \"Product Name\".",
  "concerns": [
